    {
      "id": "20bc3beeeff2cc4c7d5cb0112dfc71e3ade956c9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 298,
        "name": "Jeff Mahoney",
        "email": "jeffm@suse.com",
        "username": "jeffm"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-20 21:37:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nThe previous version built ok with SLES11 SP2 but not with 3.7. It was missing definition of &init_user_ns and HAVE_POSIXACL_USER_NS only matters for the linux version. The darwin and liblustre versions should always mask out the first argument. It turns out init_user_ns is declared in a few includes, so we use <linux/utsname.h> since it'll always be there even if the the init_user_ns declaration isn't. Saves us another #ifdef.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c1f48db3f12c244714d6daebcf6d181cc8facbe0",
      "author": {
